{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LWSNG9dDzYmuWn3UiyerrZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→from django.db import models\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→class Reservation(models.Model):\n     5→    guest_name = models.CharField(max_length=100)\n     6→    room_number = models.IntegerField()\n     7→    check_in = models.DateTimeField()\n     8→    check_out = models.DateTimeField()\n     9→    status = models.CharField(max_length=20, default=\"pending\")\n    10→\n    11→    class Meta:\n    12→        ordering = [\"-check_in\"]\n    13→\n    14→    def __str__(self):\n    15→        return f\"{self.guest_name} - Room {self.room_number}\"\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0751f4c7-557e-46b9-9468-08e7e0258419","uuid":"68d1dd6d-f8f8-48ad-a7bd-3465daaf1c4c"}
